Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> If you'd prefer to boil your green beans, skip the oven.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice
widthways into thin pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and carrot.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up
as it cooks.

While the mince and veg fry, spread the green beans out on a medium
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the green beans on the top shelf until tender,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> If you'd prefer to boil your green beans, boil them while the mince fries for
> 4-6 mins, until tender.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @red wine jus paste{15%grams},
@Worcester sauce{15%grams}, @beef stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{150%milliliter} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot
> water for 1 min to loosen.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off
the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{some} and mash
until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Share the mashed potato between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon the beef over the mash.

Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}.

Serve the green beans alongside. Enjoy!